100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On November 9, 1925, the League of Nations convened to address rising tensions in Europe, with discussions focused on disarmament and peacekeeping efforts. In the United States, a significant judicial case unfolded as the trial for the Scopes "Monkey" trial continued, igniting fierce debates over evolution and education. Meanwhile, in the Soviet Union, reports indicated a push for industrialization as the government aimed to bolster its economy.
